generic:link.msg:message: Maximum during the month>=2nd maximum during the month>=3rd maximum during the month
Minimum during the month<=2nd minimum during the month<=3rd minimum during the month

"Total Value of available intraday liquidity at the start of the business day" = (Central bank reserves + Collateral pledged at the central bank + Collateral pledged at ancillary systems + Unencumbered liquid assets on a bank's balance sheet + Total Credit Lines Available + Balances with other banks + Others)
Others (pl give details) should be sum of all child of others.
"Total value of intraday credit lines extended to customers" = (Of which secured + Of which committed + Of which used at peak usage)
"Total Credit Lines Available" = (Of Credit Lines Available + Secured + Of Credit Lines Available + Committed)
Value should be in positive.

"Largest positive net cumulative position dates" and "Largest negative net cumulative position dates" should be less than or equal to "Reporting End Date" and more than or equal to "Reporting Start Date".
"Dates of Total Value of available intraday liquidity at the start of the business day" should be less than or equal to "Reporting End Date" and more than or equal to "Reporting Start Date".
"Gross payments sent dates" and "Gross payments received dates" should be less than or equal to the "reporting end date" and more than or equal to the "reporting start date".
Time specific obligations dates should be less than or equal to the "reporting end date" and more than or equal to the "reporting start date".
"Dates related to Corresponding Banking Service" should be less than or equal to the "reporting end date" and more than or equal to the "reporting start date".
Average value should be equal to or less than maximum value during the month.
Average value should be more than or equal to minimum value during the month.
